Common Issues and Solutions
Issue: Pydantic validation errors are unclear

Solution: Catch ValidationError and iterate through e.errors() to print each error
Issue: File not found errors

Solution: Use absolute paths or verify current working directory
Issue: YAML parsing fails

Solution: Check YAML syntax, ensure proper indentation
Conclusion
You have successfully built a typed configuration loader that:

Enforces type safety using Pydantic models
Validates configuration data against defined schemas
Applies sensible defaults for optional values
Detects and reports invalid or missing configuration values
Supports multiple configuration file formats (JSON, YAML)
This pattern is essential for DevOps engineers managing application deployments across multiple environments. Type-safe configuration prevents runtime errors, ensures consistency, and makes configuration requirements explicit and self-documenting.

Key Takeaways:

Type validation catches errors before runtime
Default values reduce configuration complexity
Schema-based validation provides clear contracts
Proper error handling improves debugging experience
